COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1152, L.D. 1725
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment requires that
33 the sheriff for each county must submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee on
44 Criminal Justice and Public Safety regarding the membership status of the board of visitors
55 of each jail or other county correctional facility under the sheriff's supervision. The
66 committee may submit legislation based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the
77 132nd Legislature. The bill also makes a technical change regarding the sharing of board
88 of visitors annual reports with other boards of visitors.
